default3.7
default. 
defaultWe are not satisfied that the proposed sustainability criteria are sufficiently demanding. Wastes and residues are not subject to sustainability criteria. In theory, giving waste a free pass appear
defaults appealing, but what is “waste” and what are “residues”? The OFGEM guidance is remarkably vague and clearly capable of being exploited: “
defaultIt is not possible to lay down definitive or absolute rules as to when particular materials will be considered as 
defaultwaste materials or not”. We fear that this complexity of definition could provide the unscrupulous with a loophole to exploit.
default&#xa0;
default3.8
default. 
defaultOFGEM effectively points to the weakness of the process of operators verifying the information they supply on 
defaultsustainability: “Under the Orders, operators of generating stations for solid and gaseous biomass are not required to verify the information they provide to us in order to be eligible for ROCs”.
default Reporting of sustainability criteria appears to rely too much
default on the honesty box principle, particularly in the context of “weak governance structures” identified in the “
defaultReport from the Commission to the Council and the European Parliament on sustainability requirements for the use of solid and gaseous biomass sour
defaultces in electricity, heating and cooling” (2010).
default3.9
default. The Government issued new biomass sustainability standards on 22
defaultnd
default August 2013.  The Chief Scientist at 
